newsitem.title: AUSTRIA: Austrian bonds end soft, but upside seen.
newsitem.headline: Austrian bonds end soft, but upside seen.

text.p: Austrian bonds tracked the German Bund future lower on Thursday but traders said the uptrend remained intact.
They said the next target of 103.5 for the Bund was still attainable.
* 10-year benchmark 5.625 pct bond maturing July 2007 down 15 bps at 100.15 to yield 5.60 (5.58) pct in bourse trade, quoted post-market at 100.05/15 to yield 5.62/5.60 pct.
* Five-year 4.625 bond maturing May 2002 steady at 100.30 to yield 4.55 pct in bourse trade, quoted post-market at 100.16/24 to yield 4.58/57 percent.
* Austrian bond future down 35 bps at 110.03 on turnover of 230 lots.
* 10-year spread over Germany steady at five bps, five-year spread up one at 19 bps.
* Money market rates steady with three-month VIBOR at 3.393 and overnight money at 3.13/3.38.
